    "This case activates IC1 on two materiality triggers: a Rs 5 Cr ticket at the institutional escalation threshold, and four amplification flags in S1 synthesis at or above the compound-risk threshold. The proposal itself is architecturally uncontroversial — a fresh-inflow-funded debt sleeve to address a documented zero-debt design gap in a portfolio sitting at 89.9% equity against a 60-70% mandate band, anchored by a fit-for-purpose short-duration scheme (Kotak Bond Short Term Plan, AUM Rs 17,460 Cr, lead manager tenure 7.3 years, 3Y Sharpe 1.0552). E3 (macro), E4 (behavioural), and E7 (scheme-level) converge on directional support. G3 passes. The deliberation does not sit on whether the sleeve should exist; it sits on whether Rs 5 Cr at this composition is the right execution of the right architectural instinct.",
